Paddle hits previously used only `|vx|` (landscape) or `|vy|` (portrait). After a stone deflection, most speed could sit on the other axis тАФ the next paddle hit then reset the ball to near-crawl speed.

- [x] `nextPaddleHitSpeed()` uses `Math.hypot(vx, vy)` for paddle rebound speed
- [x] `resolveStoneCollisions()` enforces minimum speed (`initialBallSpeed ├Ч 0.55`) after stone bounce

Note: center court still has intentional **0.75├Ч** travel speed on the primary axis (`zoneMult` in `ballPhysics.ts`, middle 30% of court).

